WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:13.471 --> 00:00:16.933 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Lingalind,
a world surrounded by a wall.

00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:20.145 position:50% align:center
The wall enshrouds
the land, protecting,

00:00:20.228 --> 00:00:24.607 position:50% align:center
nurturing, sustaining.
The wall is god.

00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:29.738 position:50% align:center
It is at the very center
of life in Lingalind.

00:00:29.821 --> 00:00:33.116 position:50% align:center
On that fated day,
a man fell from the sky

00:00:33.199 --> 00:00:36.619 position:50% align:center
at the remote village
of Edger in Iki.

00:00:36.703 --> 00:00:38.663 position:50% align:center
This man of missing memories

00:00:38.747 --> 00:00:42.584 position:50% align:center
was able to control a Briheight
without conviction.

00:00:42.667 --> 00:00:44.461 position:50% align:center
He had this to say:

00:00:44.544 --> 00:00:46.671 position:50% align:center
"I'm going back
beyond the wall."

00:00:46.755 --> 00:00:48.340 position:50% align:center
To the denizens of Lingalind,

00:00:48.423 --> 00:00:52.218 position:50% align:center
he defies common sense.
His name...

00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:54.220 position:50% align:center
Arrow. Call me Back Arrow.

00:00:54.304 --> 00:00:57.015 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] Oh, come on!
Give us your real name already!

00:00:57.098 --> 00:00:59.893 position:50% align:center
You can't just tell us
to call you-- Hey! Buddy!

00:00:59.976 --> 00:01:01.686 position:50% align:center
Listen when people
are talking to you!

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:05.482 position:50% align:center
Uh. Could you maybe
put those on, please?

00:01:05.565 --> 00:01:06.983 position:50% align:center
Sure, no problem!

00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:10.320 position:50% align:center
Don't worry, this memento of
your dad's is in safe hands!

00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:12.530 position:50% align:center
I owe you one! Thanks!

00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:14.199 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:17.660 position:50% align:center
[VILLAGERS gasping]

00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:20.205 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
All right, I'm out! Later!

00:01:20.288 --> 00:01:21.414 position:50% align:center
Where are you going?

00:01:21.498 --> 00:01:22.624 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Beyond the wall!

00:01:22.707 --> 00:01:23.958 position:50% align:center
I really hate to
bail on you guys,

00:01:24.042 --> 00:01:27.462 position:50% align:center
but I've got to go back!
Take care!

00:01:27.545 --> 00:01:28.672 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Ren, let's go!

00:01:28.755 --> 00:01:30.006 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN]
Right!

00:01:36.346 --> 00:01:38.807 position:50% align:center
What is that guy's deal?

00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:40.850 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN gasps]
Atlee!

00:03:17.197 --> 00:03:22.327 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW grunting]

00:03:22.410 --> 00:03:23.870 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
I keep going and going,

00:03:23.953 --> 00:03:26.498 position:50% align:center
but it's not getting closer!

00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:36.633 position:50% align:center
And I'm starving, too! Can't
some food fall from the sky?

00:03:36.716 --> 00:03:37.967 position:50% align:center
My goodness.

00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:39.386 position:50% align:center
Eh?

00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:41.471 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] The wall's a lot bigger
than it looks, you know.

00:03:41.554 --> 00:03:43.181 position:50% align:center
It may seem close,
but it could take you

00:03:43.264 --> 00:03:45.433 position:50% align:center
months to get there from here.

00:03:45.517 --> 00:03:47.352 position:50% align:center
Can I ask who you are?

00:03:47.435 --> 00:03:50.689 position:50% align:center
You may call me Shu Bi.
But enough about me.

00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:53.066 position:50% align:center
You were in that Briheight
for five-plus hours?

00:03:53.149 --> 00:03:55.902 position:50% align:center
That's astounding! Your
conviction is something else!

00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:57.362 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Yeah, you think so?

00:03:57.445 --> 00:03:59.948 position:50% align:center
Yes, most people struggle
with one or two.

00:04:00.031 --> 00:04:01.241 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
It's just my second time,

00:04:01.324 --> 00:04:03.076 position:50% align:center
so I guess I wouldn't know.

00:04:03.159 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center
Second time?

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:07.372 position:50% align:center
I'm curious, did you really
come from beyond the wall?

00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:08.248 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:04:08.331 --> 00:04:09.624 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
What's out there?

00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:11.167 position:50% align:center
I wish I knew.

00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:13.128 position:50% align:center
But I'll find out soon enough,
when I go to the other si--

00:04:13.211 --> 00:04:16.840 position:50% align:center
There is no "other side!"
There just isn't, okay?

00:04:16.923 --> 00:04:19.676 position:50% align:center
Sorry, that sort of
reaction is normal.

00:04:19.759 --> 00:04:21.970 position:50% align:center
The wall enshrouds
the land, nurturing,

00:04:22.053 --> 00:04:23.680 position:50% align:center
and protecting those within it.

00:04:23.763 --> 00:04:25.473 position:50% align:center
Beyond, there's nothing.

00:04:25.557 --> 00:04:27.976 position:50% align:center
Our entire world,
known as Lingalind,

00:04:28.059 --> 00:04:31.604 position:50% align:center
is wholly inside the walls.
Or so people believe.

00:04:31.688 --> 00:04:32.772 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
And you?

00:04:32.856 --> 00:04:35.275 position:50% align:center
Me? One could say
that I'm a genius.

00:04:35.358 --> 00:04:36.985 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Hey, good for you.

00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:38.403 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN grunts]

00:04:38.486 --> 00:04:40.864 position:50% align:center
The wall is at least
ten-thousand gents tall.

00:04:40.947 --> 00:04:42.907 position:50% align:center
Ten-thousand gents?

00:04:42.991 --> 00:04:45.869 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] For reference,
I'm 1.78 gents tall.

00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:49.039 position:50% align:center
It's roughly 5,678 times that.

00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:52.500 position:50% align:center
Do you think that you could
scale over 5,678 me's

00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:55.003 position:50% align:center
stacked on top of each other?

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:58.173 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI groans]

00:04:58.256 --> 00:04:59.466 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN]
You despicable brute!

00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:02.260 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Ren! Stop--

00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:05.180 position:50% align:center
How dare you strike Sir Shu!

00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.975 position:50% align:center
Sorry, he just pissed me off.

00:05:09.059 --> 00:05:11.311 position:50% align:center
But the good news is I learned
that I can send one of him

00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:15.482 position:50% align:center
flying, but 5,687 him's
would probably be too much.

00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:18.610 position:50% align:center
Stop blabbering nonsense!

00:05:18.693 --> 00:05:20.612 position:50% align:center
That's far enough, Ren!

00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:23.365 position:50% align:center
Arrow, you have quite
the unique style

00:05:23.448 --> 00:05:25.158 position:50% align:center
of communication, don't you?

00:05:25.241 --> 00:05:28.161 position:50% align:center
I bet you're hungry, no?
Feel free to have that.

00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:32.874 position:50% align:center
Uh. Don't mind if I do.

00:05:32.957 --> 00:05:34.376 position:50% align:center
Yummy!

00:05:34.459 --> 00:05:37.504 position:50% align:center
Of course. It's ant-eating boar
thigh, I'd expect no less.

00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:39.756 position:50% align:center
And Ren here is a
surprisingly good cook,

00:05:39.839 --> 00:05:41.800 position:50% align:center
so naturally she
made it extra delicious.

00:05:41.883 --> 00:05:44.678 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] You can't stop me
from going to the wall. Sorry.

00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:46.012 position:50% align:center
I wasn't planning to.

00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:47.639 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Sir Shu?

00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:49.933 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] Are you gonna
help me then? Sweet!

00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:52.352 position:50% align:center
In exchange, I'd like you
to wait a few days

00:05:52.435 --> 00:05:53.853 position:50% align:center
before making your move.

00:05:53.937 --> 00:05:55.230 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:57.732 position:50% align:center
"The stars border the
heavens themselves,

00:05:57.816 --> 00:06:00.402 position:50% align:center
and the towering wall is
the edge of the world."

00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:01.945 position:50% align:center
Even I don't know enough

00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:05.448 position:50% align:center
to challenge that logic just
yet, so I'd like a little time.

00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:07.909 position:50% align:center
Give me one good reason
why I should trust you.

00:06:07.992 --> 00:06:12.205 position:50% align:center
Give me one good reason
why you should doubt me.

00:06:12.288 --> 00:06:13.665 position:50% align:center
You got me there.

00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:16.126 position:50% align:center
I can't remember anything,
so I can't come up with one.

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:18.920 position:50% align:center
I'm quite relieved to learn
that you're a man of reason.

00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:22.007 position:50% align:center
Though full disclosure, I'm
only doing this for my benefit.

00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:25.051 position:50% align:center
So you should only trust me
if it benefits you as well.

00:06:25.135 --> 00:06:26.886 position:50% align:center
Eh, I probably wouldn't
want anything to do

00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:29.639 position:50% align:center
with 5,678 of you to be fair,

00:06:29.723 --> 00:06:32.892 position:50% align:center
but I get the feeling
I can trust you.

00:06:35.437 --> 00:06:37.439 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN] Her conviction
levels are normal.

00:06:37.522 --> 00:06:40.108 position:50% align:center
Emotional levels
are fine, as well.

00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:41.860 position:50% align:center
Can I go yet?

00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:43.611 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Just rest a little longer.

00:06:43.695 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50% align:center
We know you're exhausted.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.448 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL]
But--!

00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:48.700 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN] Don't forget:
Briheights manifest by the power

00:06:48.783 --> 00:06:51.578 position:50% align:center
of one's will. The fact you're
awake at all this soon after

00:06:51.661 --> 00:06:53.538 position:50% align:center
your first time is proof
of your strength.

00:06:53.621 --> 00:06:54.998 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we're tough cookies here

00:06:55.081 --> 00:06:56.708 position:50% align:center
in Edger Village,
that's for sure.

00:06:56.791 --> 00:06:58.251 position:50% align:center
Why are you bragging, Bit?

00:06:58.335 --> 00:06:59.336 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Wait, that guy--!

00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.254 position:50% align:center
Ol panties man
ran off somewhere.

00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:02.464 position:50% align:center
We've gotta find him!

00:07:02.547 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
Even in a Briheight,
he's never gonna make it

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:05.884 position:50% align:center
all the way to the wall!

00:07:05.967 --> 00:07:08.553 position:50% align:center
You remember that guy destroyed
my house, right? Forget him!

00:07:08.636 --> 00:07:11.639 position:50% align:center
I also remember him saving me!

00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:12.807 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL gasps]

00:07:12.891 --> 00:07:14.309 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:07:14.392 --> 00:07:18.229 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW snores]

00:07:20.065 --> 00:07:21.900 position:50% align:center
It looks like he's fast asleep.

00:07:21.983 --> 00:07:23.777 position:50% align:center
What'd he even come back for?

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:26.488 position:50% align:center
[ANNIE] A scary-looking
lady dropped him off.

00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:30.200 position:50% align:center
Oh, come on, it's not
like he belongs here!

00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:33.328 position:50% align:center
Sir Shu, I have to ask, what
exactly are you planning?

00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:35.455 position:50% align:center
Hm? Why? Will you stop me
if you don't like it--?

00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:37.248 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't waste
my time trying to.

00:07:37.332 --> 00:07:38.541 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Hmph.

00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:40.460 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN]
That said, I would advise you

00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:42.253 position:50% align:center
to avoid uttering
"beyond the wall"

00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:43.755 position:50% align:center
in the imperial court.

00:07:43.838 --> 00:07:45.382 position:50% align:center
If His Majesty were
to hear something

00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.217 position:50% align:center
so blasphemous,
even you wouldn't--

00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:49.386 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Wouldn't be spared?

00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.721 position:50% align:center
Yes, yes, I know
better than that.

00:07:51.805 --> 00:07:52.889 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:58.269 position:50% align:center
Finally back, huh? Shu?

00:07:58.353 --> 00:08:00.188 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Oh? What are you doing out here

00:08:00.271 --> 00:08:01.564 position:50% align:center
this early in the morning?

00:08:01.648 --> 00:08:03.733 position:50% align:center
Coming back from a
late-night rendezvous?

00:08:03.817 --> 00:08:06.778 position:50% align:center
Whoa, what happened
to your face?

00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:09.572 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN laughs]
Did you make a move on Ren

00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:11.032 position:50% align:center
and get smacked for it?

00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:12.867 position:50% align:center
Not like I could blame her,
you probably deserved it.

00:08:12.951 --> 00:08:14.035 position:50% align:center
What? No!

00:08:14.119 --> 00:08:15.370 position:50% align:center
I was only kidding.

00:08:15.453 --> 00:08:16.996 position:50% align:center
I know this guy
doesn't have the guts

00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.249 position:50% align:center
to try something like
that on you, Ren Sin.

00:08:19.332 --> 00:08:21.167 position:50% align:center
You're so rude, Kai.

00:08:21.251 --> 00:08:23.920 position:50% align:center
And yet here I am,
waiting for your return.

00:08:24.004 --> 00:08:27.799 position:50% align:center
So, did you find the
second Rakuho? Shu?

00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:30.969 position:50% align:center
Wait one day for me.
I'll give a full report then.

00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:32.595 position:50% align:center
[KAI RHODAN]
Hmph. Be careful.

00:08:32.679 --> 00:08:34.431 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna see
my childhood friend

00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:36.349 position:50% align:center
get into trouble and
come back all bloody.

00:08:36.433 --> 00:08:38.059 position:50% align:center
Thanks, but you have
nothing to worry about.

00:08:38.143 --> 00:08:40.687 position:50% align:center
I'm famous for my thick-skin.

00:08:51.197 --> 00:08:53.366 position:50% align:center
[JIM]
Arrow! Play chopscotch!

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:56.828 position:50% align:center
You're the chopper! Split this
log with nothin' but your head!

00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:58.288 position:50% align:center
--Okay!
--[grunts]

00:08:58.371 --> 00:09:01.416 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:09:01.499 --> 00:09:02.751 position:50% align:center
--[KIDS gasping]
--[SAM] Whoa!

00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:05.754 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] All right!
Now it's my turn to throw!

00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:08.173 position:50% align:center
Ready? Here it comes!
Windin' up!

00:09:08.256 --> 00:09:10.050 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL] Try not to
bother Arrow, you guys.

00:09:10.133 --> 00:09:12.552 position:50% align:center
He's tired. At least,
I assume he is.

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.679 position:50% align:center
[JIM]
Run! It's the sheriff!

00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:16.556 position:50% align:center
[KIDS laughing]

00:09:16.639 --> 00:09:19.017 position:50% align:center
Sorry about them, they like
to mess with people.

00:09:19.100 --> 00:09:21.519 position:50% align:center
Hey, thanks to their game,
I know I've got a hard head,

00:09:21.603 --> 00:09:23.480 position:50% align:center
so you could say
they did me a favor.

00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:24.522 position:50% align:center
You're bleeding!

00:09:24.606 --> 00:09:25.940 position:50% align:center
Eh?

00:09:30.236 --> 00:09:33.114 position:50% align:center
Thanks for this. Oh,
and for the clothes, too.

00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:34.366 position:50% align:center
You can thank bit for that one.

00:09:34.449 --> 00:09:35.617 position:50% align:center
Oh?

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:38.453 position:50% align:center
He sewed you that outfit
entirely from scraps.

00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:40.288 position:50% align:center
He's the best tailor
in the whole town!

00:09:40.372 --> 00:09:42.290 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Sucks at shooting, though.

00:09:42.374 --> 00:09:44.459 position:50% align:center
--Shuddap.
--[BACK ARROW] Really?

00:09:44.542 --> 00:09:45.794 position:50% align:center
You got a problem with 'em?

00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:48.338 position:50% align:center
Nah, they're well made!

00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:51.049 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
I like 'em!

00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:53.051 position:50% align:center
Well, that doesn't
mean I like you.

00:09:53.134 --> 00:09:56.554 position:50% align:center
But you did save Atlee.
Consider your debt repaid.

00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:58.306 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
What debt? I never owed you.

00:09:58.390 --> 00:10:00.266 position:50% align:center
You destroyed my house,
remember?

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:05.897 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah! Sorry about that, man!
Well, I'll just rebuild it!

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:07.941 position:50% align:center
That should do!

00:10:08.024 --> 00:10:10.276 position:50% align:center
What even is this?
'Cus it's not a house.

00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:11.861 position:50% align:center
It will be, though!

00:10:11.945 --> 00:10:14.072 position:50% align:center
I'll add a roof and walls once I
find us some better materials.

00:10:14.155 --> 00:10:16.324 position:50% align:center
What does that mean?
You're staying?

00:10:16.408 --> 00:10:17.992 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Uhh...

00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:19.452 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Listen.

00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:21.621 position:50% align:center
Don't you think it's likely you
ran away from your home,

00:10:21.705 --> 00:10:24.582 position:50% align:center
or something? Probably
using that Rakuho?

00:10:24.666 --> 00:10:26.459 position:50% align:center
Then you must have lost
control, hit your head,

00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:28.378 position:50% align:center
and lost your memories.

00:10:28.461 --> 00:10:31.089 position:50% align:center
Right? Or is this amnesia
thing all just an act?

00:10:31.172 --> 00:10:33.800 position:50% align:center
That's what I've been thinking
since we interrogated him.

00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:34.801 position:50% align:center
So what's your deal?

00:10:34.884 --> 00:10:36.636 position:50% align:center
I know I came from
beyond the wall.

00:10:36.720 --> 00:10:39.514 position:50% align:center
But that's really
all I remember.

00:10:43.018 --> 00:10:44.561 position:50% align:center
[BURK LEAN]
Mm-hm.

00:10:46.187 --> 00:10:46.980 position:50% align:center
Come on.

00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:47.856 position:50% align:center
Elsha?

00:10:47.939 --> 00:10:51.026 position:50% align:center
Sit this one out, Atlee. Hey.

00:10:51.109 --> 00:10:52.610 position:50% align:center
What are we doin'?

00:10:52.694 --> 00:10:56.448 position:50% align:center
[gunshots]

00:10:56.531 --> 00:10:59.325 position:50% align:center
Man, just four shots?
Nice work, Elsha!

00:10:59.409 --> 00:11:00.869 position:50% align:center
Bet it's tasty!

00:11:00.952 --> 00:11:04.914 position:50% align:center
Look there. That's our Edger
Village over across that gap.

00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:07.667 position:50% align:center
We have to hunt for food and
grow what little vegetables

00:11:07.751 --> 00:11:11.629 position:50% align:center
we can. Honestly,
we're barely surviving.

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:14.341 position:50% align:center
That's just how it is
in our little town.

00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:16.092 position:50% align:center
See how small it is?

00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:18.970 position:50% align:center
I guess, but I wouldn't know,
I haven't been anywhere else.

00:11:19.054 --> 00:11:21.639 position:50% align:center
You know that group of
kids Atlee looks after?

00:11:21.723 --> 00:11:24.142 position:50% align:center
None of them have
any parents anymore.

00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:26.478 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Epidemics, hunting accidents.

00:11:26.561 --> 00:11:29.189 position:50% align:center
Lots of things kill people here.

00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:32.525 position:50% align:center
To be frank, Atlee, Bit and I
lost our parents, too.

00:11:32.609 --> 00:11:35.403 position:50% align:center
Which is why we can't afford
to take on additional risk.

00:11:35.487 --> 00:11:36.821 position:50% align:center
You mean me?

00:11:36.905 --> 00:11:39.491 position:50% align:center
Thugs will hunt your Rakuho
down, and that's a fact.

00:11:39.574 --> 00:11:42.827 position:50% align:center
I'm surprised it's so tough.
You all seem to like it here.

00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:45.705 position:50% align:center
All of us are just trying
to live life to the fullest.

00:11:45.789 --> 00:11:47.415 position:50% align:center
Because tomorrow might not come.

00:11:47.499 --> 00:11:50.210 position:50% align:center
Can't you guys just pack it up
and find somewhere else to live?

00:11:50.293 --> 00:11:52.212 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] Where?
For your information,

00:11:52.295 --> 00:11:55.090 position:50% align:center
Rekka and Lutoh are
in a huge war right now!

00:11:55.173 --> 00:11:56.966 position:50% align:center
Our ancestors got
pushed out of their lands

00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.719 position:50% align:center
and had to come here,
to this barren, desolate place.

00:11:59.803 --> 00:12:01.137 position:50% align:center
They had to get on
their hands and knees

00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:02.931 position:50% align:center
and beg Iki for
permission to live here.

00:12:03.014 --> 00:12:04.974 position:50% align:center
A place with barely
enough resources

00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:06.101 position:50% align:center
to keep everyone alive!

00:12:06.184 --> 00:12:08.311 position:50% align:center
There's always outside.

00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:10.063 position:50% align:center
You just gotta go
beyond the wall.

00:12:10.146 --> 00:12:15.026 position:50% align:center
[gasps] We keep telling
you, it doesn't exist.

00:12:15.110 --> 00:12:17.904 position:50% align:center
And I'm sorry, but we
can't support a stranger,

00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:20.990 position:50% align:center
let alone follow impossible
dreams like yours.

00:12:21.074 --> 00:12:22.158 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Hm?

00:12:22.242 --> 00:12:23.743 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
You can take the hornhare,

00:12:23.827 --> 00:12:26.705 position:50% align:center
but I'm afraid you
can't stay any longer.

00:12:26.788 --> 00:12:30.041 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] And these, too.
Water and dried deerhorse.

00:12:30.125 --> 00:12:33.503 position:50% align:center
It's not much, but it's
the best we can do for you.

00:12:42.220 --> 00:12:44.848 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] Here's the plan: you
keep an eye on Edger Village.

00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.433 position:50% align:center
While you're doing that,
I'll stay here--

00:12:46.516 --> 00:12:48.560 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN] I know you're doing
something dangerous. What is it?

00:12:48.643 --> 00:12:51.938 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] I had a feeling I
couldn't hide it from you. Look.

00:12:52.022 --> 00:12:55.817 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Is that the seal to
enter the banned texts archive?

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:57.777 position:50% align:center
Only His Majesty
and the prime minister

00:12:57.861 --> 00:12:59.362 position:50% align:center
are supposed to have one.

00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:01.489 position:50% align:center
I just knew such
a time would come.

00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:02.991 position:50% align:center
[REN SIN]
Did you make a copy o--?

00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.493 position:50% align:center
Watch your voice, we don't
want to be overheard.

00:13:05.577 --> 00:13:06.619 position:50% align:center
We're short on time as it is,

00:13:06.703 --> 00:13:07.996 position:50% align:center
and I have a lot
to figure out before

00:13:08.079 --> 00:13:10.999 position:50% align:center
the world reacts to
our man in the Rakuho.

00:13:11.082 --> 00:13:13.084 position:50% align:center
The bandit who attacked
Edger Village likely

00:13:13.168 --> 00:13:16.671 position:50% align:center
worked for Lutoh, which
means they'll know soon.

00:13:19.507 --> 00:13:20.967 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA]
Your Bind Warper?

00:13:21.051 --> 00:13:22.510 position:50% align:center
[DEBUGGER]
Yes.

00:13:22.594 --> 00:13:24.512 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA]
Indeed, it's broken.

00:13:24.596 --> 00:13:26.765 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE]
A man was in the Rakuho you say?

00:13:26.848 --> 00:13:28.641 position:50% align:center
Not only that, but when
you lost the battle,

00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:31.436 position:50% align:center
you survived while your
Bind Warper broke?

00:13:31.519 --> 00:13:34.272 position:50% align:center
This goes against
everything that we know.

00:13:34.356 --> 00:13:35.899 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Hm?

00:13:38.026 --> 00:13:40.445 position:50% align:center
I happened to hear
your conversation.

00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:43.073 position:50% align:center
Is this not a
tremendous discovery?

00:13:43.156 --> 00:13:45.700 position:50% align:center
No, you need not concern
yourself, Princess.

00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:48.078 position:50% align:center
Wait, Princess?
As in Fine FortÃ©?

00:13:48.161 --> 00:13:50.163 position:50% align:center
Begone. Your presence is
insulting to the princess.

00:13:50.246 --> 00:13:53.625 position:50% align:center
No, I don't mind. Though I
do have a question for you.

00:13:53.708 --> 00:13:55.460 position:50% align:center
Are you the man
I've heard about?

00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.462 position:50% align:center
The one that has been
working for our Lutoh?

00:13:57.545 --> 00:13:58.797 position:50% align:center
[DEBUGGER]
Yes.

00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:00.423 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE]
Princess, you really shouldn't.

00:14:00.507 --> 00:14:02.217 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA] He's lowborn.
You're wasting your--

00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:04.552 position:50% align:center
It's okay. Raise your head.

00:14:04.636 --> 00:14:05.804 position:50% align:center
[DEBUGGER]
Of course.

00:14:05.887 --> 00:14:07.972 position:50% align:center
People in your line of
work are very helpful

00:14:08.056 --> 00:14:11.059 position:50% align:center
when our military can't act
for one reason or another.

00:14:11.142 --> 00:14:12.227 position:50% align:center
You have my thanks.

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
[DEBUGGER]
No. I don't deserve it.

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:16.439 position:50% align:center
Why must people
kill each other?

00:14:16.523 --> 00:14:18.400 position:50% align:center
I want to solve conflict
without death.

00:14:18.483 --> 00:14:19.401 position:50% align:center
[DEBUGGER]
Huh?

00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:20.860 position:50% align:center
If it's possible...

00:14:20.944 --> 00:14:24.155 position:50% align:center
If no one has to die when
we fight with Briheights,

00:14:24.239 --> 00:14:27.992 position:50% align:center
then I'd really like to know
how the Rakuho man does it.

00:14:28.076 --> 00:14:30.078 position:50% align:center
I wish I could meet him.

00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.496 position:50% align:center
My Princess.

00:14:31.579 --> 00:14:34.499 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA] But if we marched
our troops over there...

00:14:34.582 --> 00:14:36.376 position:50% align:center
Rekka'd throw a fit.

00:14:36.459 --> 00:14:39.629 position:50% align:center
Yes, I know. But that man
could very well be the key

00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:40.964 position:50% align:center
which leads to world peace,

00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:42.757 position:50% align:center
and that may be worth
taking some risks.

00:14:42.841 --> 00:14:45.468 position:50% align:center
I fully understand your
peace-loving heart.

00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:48.513 position:50% align:center
I, Peath Glinhouse will see that
something be done at once.

00:14:48.596 --> 00:14:49.389 position:50% align:center
You will?

00:14:49.472 --> 00:14:51.099 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:14:51.182 --> 00:14:52.851 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE]
It's really that simple.

00:14:52.934 --> 00:14:55.311 position:50% align:center
Isn't Edger Village
your territory?

00:14:55.395 --> 00:14:56.896 position:50% align:center
I wish I could help,
Secretary Peath,

00:14:56.980 --> 00:14:58.314 position:50% align:center
but we're an independent nation.

00:14:58.398 --> 00:15:00.817 position:50% align:center
Even if you're the one
asking, we can't help.

00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:02.986 position:50% align:center
And we may be weak,
but bossing us around

00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.362 position:50% align:center
isn't going to get you anywhere.

00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:06.948 position:50% align:center
President Garay.
Might it interest you to know

00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:08.950 position:50% align:center
that unlike our
kind-hearted princess,

00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:11.828 position:50% align:center
many of us here are itching
for the chance to battle?

00:15:11.911 --> 00:15:16.332 position:50% align:center
I understand. What exactly
are you asking us to do?

00:15:18.209 --> 00:15:19.961 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
What's with all this meat?

00:15:20.045 --> 00:15:22.339 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL] I wonder if
this is Arrow's doing.

00:15:22.422 --> 00:15:24.841 position:50% align:center
If it is, he's sure
hung up on paying debts.

00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:27.260 position:50% align:center
[horn blares]

00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:29.512 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
Listen up, Edger Villagers!

00:15:29.596 --> 00:15:32.474 position:50% align:center
We're from the Iki Territory's
Self-Defense Force!

00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:35.352 position:50% align:center
Military? What for?

00:15:35.435 --> 00:15:37.437 position:50% align:center
I, Commander Tyrone Duster,

00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:39.731 position:50% align:center
have been given authority
to do what I please!

00:15:39.814 --> 00:15:42.525 position:50% align:center
And I order the village
to be searched! Do it.

00:15:42.609 --> 00:15:43.651 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIERS]
Yes, sir!

00:15:43.735 --> 00:15:46.237 position:50% align:center
[gasps] What? Why?

00:15:46.321 --> 00:15:48.490 position:50% align:center
Ahh! I'm sorry!

00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:51.242 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
Don't panic!

00:15:51.326 --> 00:15:54.788 position:50% align:center
If you just do what I say,
nobody gets hurt!

00:15:54.871 --> 00:15:57.582 position:50% align:center
This is awesome! I've
always wanted to say that!

00:15:57.665 --> 00:15:59.918 position:50% align:center
I don't get it, what's
the point of this search?

00:16:00.001 --> 00:16:01.294 position:50% align:center
You must be the chief!

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:03.296 position:50% align:center
Then I'll get right
down to business.

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:05.423 position:50% align:center
Hand over the man who
landed in the Rakuho

00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:07.550 position:50% align:center
and we'll be on our way!

00:16:07.634 --> 00:16:08.843 position:50% align:center
If he's what you're looking for,

00:16:08.927 --> 00:16:10.679 position:50% align:center
you're out of luck.
He already left.

00:16:10.762 --> 00:16:14.933 position:50% align:center
He what? I imagine you heard
that? Right, Mr. President?

00:16:15.016 --> 00:16:17.894 position:50% align:center
Enough. Make the
problem disappear.

00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:19.604 position:50% align:center
We've already got
Lutoh on our case,

00:16:19.688 --> 00:16:20.939 position:50% align:center
we don't need Rekka, too.

00:16:21.022 --> 00:16:24.109 position:50% align:center
Erase Edger Village
from the map.

00:16:24.192 --> 00:16:26.111 position:50% align:center
Yes, sir!

00:16:26.194 --> 00:16:27.362 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:29.656 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
All troops, prepare for battle!

00:16:29.739 --> 00:16:32.867 position:50% align:center
Burn the village!
Slaughter 'em all! Got it?

00:16:32.951 --> 00:16:36.037 position:50% align:center
Make no mistake,
this is not a drill!

00:16:36.121 --> 00:16:38.248 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER laughs]
I've always wanted

00:16:38.331 --> 00:16:41.626 position:50% align:center
to say that line, too! [laughs]

00:16:41.710 --> 00:16:44.671 position:50% align:center
This is the real deal,
now let's get to it!

00:16:44.754 --> 00:16:46.423 position:50% align:center
[VILLAGERS scream]

00:16:46.506 --> 00:16:48.842 position:50% align:center
Ah! Not my house again!

00:16:48.925 --> 00:16:51.469 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL] Stop it!
Arrow isn't here anymore!

00:16:51.553 --> 00:16:52.595 position:50% align:center
He's long gone!

00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:54.431 position:50% align:center
Come on Atlee! Not this again!

00:16:54.514 --> 00:16:57.225 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL] All right?
So stop harassing our village!

00:16:57.308 --> 00:16:59.144 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER] You brought
out a Briheight, huh?

00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:01.896 position:50% align:center
Sounds like you're resisting!

00:17:01.980 --> 00:17:05.066 position:50% align:center
I'll destroy the village!
I know that sounds bad,

00:17:05.150 --> 00:17:07.652 position:50% align:center
but I'm in a tough position
having to make a sacrifice

00:17:07.736 --> 00:17:09.946 position:50% align:center
for the greater good and all!

00:17:10.030 --> 00:17:12.282 position:50% align:center
Man, just runnin' through these
awesome quotes today!

00:17:12.365 --> 00:17:16.161 position:50% align:center
I'll say it again! This is a
small sacrifice for the gre--

00:17:16.244 --> 00:17:19.247 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL]
That's a terrible thing to say!

00:17:21.332 --> 00:17:22.667 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER groans]

00:17:22.751 --> 00:17:28.423 position:50% align:center
I got bad news for you, lady!
My conviction is...

00:17:28.506 --> 00:17:31.176 position:50% align:center
Don't get roped into things!

00:17:31.259 --> 00:17:38.308 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL screaming]

00:17:38.391 --> 00:17:42.145 position:50% align:center
Ugh! Please tell me there's
another Warper in here!

00:17:42.228 --> 00:17:43.730 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL screams]

00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:45.774 position:50% align:center
Why does everyone who has
a bone to pick with us

00:17:45.857 --> 00:17:47.275 position:50% align:center
have to fight like
an utter maniac?

00:17:47.359 --> 00:17:51.029 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] Yes! I actually
found one! Talk about lucky!

00:17:51.112 --> 00:17:52.947 position:50% align:center
I had a feeling there might
be another Bind Warper

00:17:53.031 --> 00:17:56.701 position:50% align:center
in the Rakuho! Now.

00:17:56.785 --> 00:17:57.660 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:17:57.744 --> 00:17:59.245 position:50% align:center
Elsha!

00:17:59.329 --> 00:18:03.333 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER] What? There's
two Briheights in this place?

00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:06.503 position:50% align:center
I'm the one who told Arrow
he had to leave the village.

00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:08.922 position:50% align:center
So I've gotta step up!

00:18:09.005 --> 00:18:13.760 position:50% align:center
Whoa. Elsha was able
to make a Briheight too!

00:18:16.805 --> 00:18:21.601 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] Let Atlee go!
If you don't, I'll--

00:18:21.685 --> 00:18:22.811 position:50% align:center
Eh?

00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:30.652 position:50% align:center
Elsha! You still alive
down there? Hey!

00:18:30.735 --> 00:18:32.612 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
That was anticlimactic!

00:18:32.696 --> 00:18:35.949 position:50% align:center
But I can't believe you
had two Briheights!

00:18:36.032 --> 00:18:38.410 position:50% align:center
I think I get Mr. President now.

00:18:38.493 --> 00:18:42.872 position:50% align:center
A village this dangerous
should be wiped out!

00:18:42.956 --> 00:18:46.918 position:50% align:center
[VILLAGERS screaming]

00:18:47.002 --> 00:18:48.670 position:50% align:center
[ATLEE ARIEL gasping]

00:18:48.753 --> 00:18:50.839 position:50% align:center
Atlee, take off
the Bind Warper, now!

00:18:50.922 --> 00:18:52.340 position:50% align:center
Okay!

00:18:55.343 --> 00:18:57.387 position:50% align:center
This can't be happening!

00:18:57.470 --> 00:18:59.597 position:50% align:center
It's all because of
that bizarre man!

00:18:59.681 --> 00:19:04.144 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL] I can't take it
anymore! I'm hiding in the well!

00:19:04.227 --> 00:19:05.562 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna die!

00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:09.524 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Hey! Buddy! Yo!

00:19:09.607 --> 00:19:12.360 position:50% align:center
What the hell happened up there
while I was asleep, huh?

00:19:12.444 --> 00:19:13.611 position:50% align:center
Wait a sec, Arrow?

00:19:13.695 --> 00:19:15.363 position:50% align:center
What in the world were
you doing down there?

00:19:15.447 --> 00:19:16.865 position:50% align:center
Well, it is refreshing.

00:19:16.948 --> 00:19:19.367 position:50% align:center
But I promised some Shu guy
I'd stay here for a bit,

00:19:19.451 --> 00:19:21.161 position:50% align:center
so I had to find somewhere
I could hang out

00:19:21.244 --> 00:19:22.203 position:50% align:center
without getting in your way.

00:19:22.287 --> 00:19:24.080 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Ah! It's him!

00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:25.915 position:50% align:center
He's gonna completely
destroy the place!

00:19:25.999 --> 00:19:30.045 position:50% align:center
He what? Hey jerk! The hell
you doin' to my village?

00:19:30.128 --> 00:19:31.421 position:50% align:center
Go get him, Arrow!

00:19:31.504 --> 00:19:33.340 position:50% align:center
Not your village, but you're
helpin' us, so whatever!

00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:34.758 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
What are you talking about?

00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:38.511 position:50% align:center
I inherited the spirit
of the former sheriff!

00:19:38.595 --> 00:19:41.139 position:50% align:center
If I don't protect this
place, then who will?

00:19:41.222 --> 00:19:42.015 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:19:42.098 --> 00:19:43.975 position:50% align:center
Spirit of the sheriff?

00:19:44.059 --> 00:19:46.978 position:50% align:center
Do you think he could mean
that old pair of underwear?

00:19:47.062 --> 00:19:49.230 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
Huh... Looks empty inside,

00:19:49.314 --> 00:19:51.858 position:50% align:center
but I guess I'll haul
it back just in case.

00:19:51.941 --> 00:19:56.529 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW yelling]

00:19:56.613 --> 00:19:59.032 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Bring it on, bad guy!

00:20:06.831 --> 00:20:12.379 position:50% align:center
And now, for the most-forbidden
text about Rakuho there is!

00:20:12.462 --> 00:20:15.632 position:50% align:center
Ancient letters, huh?

00:20:15.715 --> 00:20:18.301 position:50% align:center
I think this part says,
"One who comes from beyond

00:20:18.385 --> 00:20:22.347 position:50% align:center
sleeps at the edge
of land." Beyond!

00:20:27.018 --> 00:20:30.188 position:50% align:center
What the--? Where am I?

00:20:30.271 --> 00:20:32.440 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
A Briheight lay before you.

00:20:32.524 --> 00:20:35.610 position:50% align:center
Will you agree to register
as the startup system for it?

00:20:35.694 --> 00:20:37.445 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] Whatever!
Just get me outta here!

00:20:37.529 --> 00:20:42.283 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER] Startup conviction
has been confirmed.

00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:48.373 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
So are you the Rakuho guy?

00:20:48.456 --> 00:20:49.666 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
What if I am?

00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:53.420 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
Then I'll make you disappear!

00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:55.839 position:50% align:center
That's some strange defense!

00:20:55.922 --> 00:20:57.132 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
You're not half bad!

00:20:57.215 --> 00:21:01.219 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
Bet I've trained more than you!

00:21:01.302 --> 00:21:02.470 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Doesn't matter.

00:21:02.554 --> 00:21:06.808 position:50% align:center
I won't forgive you for
attacking my village!

00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:09.728 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW grunts]

00:21:09.811 --> 00:21:12.105 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER grunts]

00:21:12.188 --> 00:21:14.024 position:50% align:center
[TYRONE DUSTER]
So fast!

00:21:14.107 --> 00:21:16.192 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Bam, bam, bam, bam!

00:21:23.700 --> 00:21:26.745 position:50% align:center
What the--? How am I not dead?

00:21:26.828 --> 00:21:30.623 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
In your face! Huh? Huh...?

00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:33.460 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] "The edge of land"
refers to Edger Village.

00:21:33.543 --> 00:21:36.171 position:50% align:center
There, "one from beyond sleeps."

00:21:36.254 --> 00:21:38.506 position:50% align:center
That man falling there
was no random event,

00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:41.843 position:50% align:center
it was destined to happen!
"The encircled world flourished,

00:21:41.926 --> 00:21:45.388 position:50% align:center
and once again,
lives tied together."

00:21:45.472 --> 00:21:48.266 position:50% align:center
But when the newcomer
reaches self-realization,

00:21:48.350 --> 00:21:50.685 position:50% align:center
the world will be destroyed.

00:21:50.769 --> 00:21:53.146 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI grunts]
Destroyed?

00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:00.945 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
So on that fated day,

00:22:01.029 --> 00:22:03.156 position:50% align:center
what happened at the
remote village of Edger

00:22:03.239 --> 00:22:05.367 position:50% align:center
put the world in motion.

00:22:05.450 --> 00:22:07.077 position:50% align:center
But the question remains:

00:22:07.160 --> 00:22:10.205 position:50% align:center
Is that which appeared
the world's hope?

00:22:10.288 --> 00:22:13.083 position:50% align:center
Or the herald of destruction?